+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XUwQAHtradFEWXWQ7NfD1T","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conclave requires API keys which aren't available. I'll proceed with autopilot mode using my own judgment for each design decision.\n\n**Design Decision: Autopilot Mode (no consensus available)**\n\nLet me work through the key design questions:\n\n**Q1: simulate() - Dependency ordering approach**\n→ Choosing: **Iterative queue-based approach (Kahn's algorithm variant)**\nReasoning: For ~220 gates, build a map of wire→gates-that-need-it, start with gates whose inputs are all in the initial values, process them, and add newly-ready gates to the queue. This is O(n) and clean. A simpler \"keep looping until all done\" approach also works for 220 gates but is less elegant.\n\n**Q2: findSwappedWires() - Algorithm approach**\n→ Choosing: **Structural pattern matching against known ripple-carry adder pattern**\nReasoning: Since we know the circuit is a ripple-carry adder with a specific structure (half adder for bit 0, full adders for remaining bits), we can analyze each bit position and check if each gate's role matches the expected pattern. Any gate whose output violates the expected role indicates a swap. This is O(n) and far superior to brute-force.\n\nLet me now write the design document."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":580,"cache_read_input_tokens":24393,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":580},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1a4f711a-8623-4fc1-9563-084b36330cf6","uuid":"ec572813-83e1-4cd8-a951-c454f74f5465"}
